items.description:
1. Apply yellow concealer underneath the eyes and on any dark spots (For fair skin, use pink).
2. Apply a second layer of concealer in your own skin tone on top of the first to even out the shade.
3. Apply cream blush to the apples of the cheeks and blend.
4. Apply contour powder beneath the cheekbones.
5. Use short, hair-like strokes with a pencil to fill in sparse brows.
6. Finish look with lip balm and mascara.

items.description:
Beauty blogger Arshia shows off her method of achieving the perfect smokey eye using just an eyeliner pencil:

1. Line upper lashline with black eyeliner pencil
2. Blend liner up to the outer corner of the eyelid with a beauty blender or fluffy brush.
3. Line lower lashline with same black eyeliner pencil.
4. Smudge liner.
5. Repeat steps 1-4 for a more dramatic look. 
6. Finish with mascara.
